article.headline: Jackson State 65, Tougaloo 52
article.story: JACKSON, Miss. (AP) -- Kelly Ross scored 19 points, including 12 in the first half, to lead Jackson State to a 65-52 win Saturday night over Tougaloo. Jackson State (3-7) was never really challenged. Tougaloo (4-5), a member of the NAIA, trailed by double-digits in the first half, but got five straight points from Donta Yates to close within nine, 36-27, about three minutes into the second half. Yates led Tougaloo with 21 points and Dennis Holder added 12. Jackson State outscored Tougaloo 14-5 over the next four minutes to stretch the lead back to 50-32 with 13 minutes left and the Tigers cruised to the victory. Jackson State jumped out to a 20-10 lead with 12 minutes left in the first half. Ross' 12 first-half points helped Jackson State take a 34-22 halftime lead. Tougaloo shot only 34 percent from the field and committed 23 turnovers. Jackson State got 12 points from Antonio Parker and 14 rebounds from Ernest Hassell.
